Rent is $749 a month. There is an all inclusive utilities fee of $129/mo - this covers your Cable TV (Spectrum 248 channels of entertainment for you),  Netflix, High Speed Wireless, Internet (up to 48 mbps), A/C, water, heat, gas, free use of laundry facilities,  Netflix and free assigned parking.<br>
<br>
If you applied for these utilities separately on your name and account, it would easily cost you at least $350 a month. So this is a big big savings for you!<br>
<br>
This is much like staying at a Residence Inn, Hyatt Place or Courtyard by Marriott except you don't have to pay the $120 hotel daily rate (yes save that money instead!). <br>
<br>
Also, you don't have the "sardine-can" like environment of an apartment. We have rented our bedrooms through AirBNB in the past for as much as $75 a day! So at $749 a month is only $24.96 a day<br>
<br>
The house is on Meadow Brook Road (Meadow Brook Hills) but is set back 200 feet so you can't hear the street noise. The place is quiet, tranquil, peaceful and has lots of privacy. This spacious furnished room for rent is on the 2nd floor where there are 3 dedicated guest rooms including this one. Two are already taken - one by a Sales Mgr for meat processing company (long term lease) and the other by a Respiratory Therapist (also long term lease). Both of them are like family - quiet, friendly, professional and personable . What is waiting for you:<br>
<br>
1. Bed (queen) / walk-in closet<br>
2. Your own small refrigerator in the room<br>
3. Central heat and a/c<br>
4. Beautiful view of nature from your bedroom window<br>
5. Absolute peace and quiet (neighbors in front, on the sides and in the back are at least 300 feet away)<br>
6. 146-channel Spectrum (Charter) TV entertainment package and Netflix<br>
7. Hi-Speed Charter Internet (probably double the speed you are used to.)<br>
8. Your own assigned parking space (yes, no need to parking on the street or looking for a free spot in an apartment complex)<br>
9. Dusk-to-dawn security lights on the parking area and security cameras on common areas.<br>
10. Free use of washer and dryer, shared refrigerator and microwave.<br>
11. Free use of the Business Office / wireless printer on the main floor.<br>
<br>
NEXT STEP <br>
1. If interested,  TEXT FIRST  <a href="#" class="show-contact" title="click to show contact info" data-href="/reply/bhm/apa/7515534713/__SERVICE_ID__" rel="nofollow">show contact info</a>
 and we will call you back. And we'll set up an an appointment for you to check out the place (this is first come, first serve)<br>
2. 6 month-lease, then month-to-month thereafter.<br>
<br>
Housing is difficult and/or expensive in Birmingham. So this set up is rare. Some of our clean guests/tenants have included a medical doctor, construction salesman, a business analyst, a gov't IT consultant, electrical engineer, a UA law student, a database developer, QA analyst, robotic engineer for car mfg co in Tuscaloosa, etc.<br>
<br>
The owner, an IT professional, works out of town and comes back to the house two weekends a month to spend time with his kids and occupies the masters bedroom on the main floor. The 3 rental rooms are on the 2nd floor.<br>
<br>
Please note again: You are assigned your own parking spot, the entry way is well-lit. For the safety and security of the tenants, security camera monitors the common areas.<br>
<br>
After 14 months of stay, an engineer who had to leave as he was relocated said:<br>
"I love this place, it was really home for me. Hate to leave, hope I will get posted again in Birmingham and I will call John."<br>
A recent guest/tenant that stayed in the place (business analyst) wrote below:<br>
<br>
